Blurb::
Choose how each constraint is scaled

Description::
Type of scaling to apply to nonlinear constraints: \c 'none', \c
'value', \c 'auto' or \c 'log'.  If a single string is specified it
will apply to all components of the relevant nonlinear constraint
vector.

See the scaling information under specific methods, e.g.,
method-*-scaling for details on how to use this keyword.

